    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<ul>\n<li>Download FernFlower.jar: <a href=\"https://the.bytecode.club/fernflower.jar\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://the.bytecode.club/fernflower.jar</a></li>\n<li>Documentation: <a href=\"http://the.bytecode.club/fernflower.txt\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://the.bytecode.club/fernflower.txt</a></li>\n<li>Repository: <a href=\"https://github.com/JetBrains/intellij-community/tree/master/plugins/java-decompiler/engine/src/org/jetbrains/java/decompiler\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://github.com/JetBrains/intellij-community/tree/master/plugins/java-decompiler/engine/src/org/jetbrains/java/decompiler</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Run &quot;<code>java -jar fernflower.jar -dgs=true JarToDecompile.jar DecompiledJar</code>&quot;</p>\n<p>This is what IntelliJ &amp; Android-Studio Decompiler does.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>\n<p>Fernflower extracts the <code>.java</code> files to a <code>.jar</code> file.</p>\n<p>You can either Unzip the jar file as a regular zip file OR you can do <code>jar xf DecompiledJar</code> and it'll extract it.</p>\n<p>Example (all in one command -- multiple commands separated by <code>&amp;&amp;</code>):</p>\n<pre><code>java -jar fernflower.jar -dgs=true JarToDecompile.jar DecompiledJar &amp;&amp; cd DecompiledJar &amp;&amp; jar xf DecompiledJar.jar &amp;&amp; cd ../\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
