  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/39563843/how-to-extract-the-source-code-from-a-jar-file-on-a-mac",
  "title" : "How to extract the source code from a *.jar file on a Mac?",
  "body" : "<p>I'm very confused. I downloaded a *.jar file as a bit of software. So, I would like to extract the source code to look at it</p>\n\n<p>I used the command <code>jar xf filename.jar</code></p>\n\n<p>which returned two more <code>*.jar</code> files and a <code>*.class</code> file. I still cannot open these in the terminal with standard text editors. </p>\n\n<p>Perhaps this is not open source software? Is there an alternative to see what has been done here?</p>\n"
